JSE-listed Datatec&rsquo;s Logicalis subsidiary has acquired a 51% stake in Openstack software-based cloud company NubeliU. &ldquo;This acquisition is an important step for Logicalis to enhance its position as a leading cloud integrator,&rdquo; Datatec CEO Jens Montanana said in a statement on Tuesday. He noted that the acquisition is part of Logicalis&rsquo;s strategy to position itself as a cloud integrator and strengthens its commitment to the opensource community, in particular with OpenStack, which is essential for large Software Defined everything, or SDx, and cloud computing projects.